The paper describes a new platform and user environment for the Coq interactive proof assistant, targeting educational use and running inside a browser. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with formal methods, automated reasoning, and theorem proving. Additionally, the paper mentions the implementation of a new serialization-based protocol for interaction with the proof assistant, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the support for popular books and libraries, which could relate to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) or Emerging Technologies (cs.ET).
